'''布加洛運動'''，其擁護者通常被称为'''布加洛男孩'''（{{lang-en|boogaloo boys/bois}}）<ref name="SPLC-2">{{Cite web|title=The 'Boogaloo' Started as a Racist Meme|url=https://www.splcenter.org/hatewatch/2020/06/05/boogaloo-started-racist-meme|accessdate=2020-06-21|author=Miller|date=2020-06-05|first=Cassie|work=[[南方贫困法律中心|南方贫困法律中心]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200620153143/https://www.splcenter.org/hatewatch/2020/06/05/boogaloo-started-racist-meme|archivedate=2020-06-20|language=en}}</ref>，是一個鬆散的美国[[極右派|极右翼]]、反政府和[[極端主義|极端主义]]運動<ref>{{cite news |title=美反政府激進右翼Boogaloo冒起受關注 |url=https://news.mingpao.com/pns/%E5%9C%8B%E9%9A%9B/article/20200619/s00014/1592504757993/%E7%BE%8E%E5%8F%8D%E6%94%BF%E5%BA%9C%E6%BF%80%E9%80%B2%E5%8F%B3%E7%BF%BCboogaloo%E5%86%92%E8%B5%B7%E5%8F%97%E9%97%9C%E6%B3%A8 |accessdate=2020-10-17 |work=[[明报|明报]] |date=2020-06-19 |language=zh-hk |archive-date=2020-10-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201022060008/https://news.mingpao.com/pns/%e5%9c%8b%e9%9a%9b/article/20200619/s00014/1592504757993/%e7%be%8e%e5%8f%8d%e6%94%bf%e5%ba%9c%e6%bf%80%e9%80%b2%e5%8f%b3%e7%bf%bcboogaloo%e5%86%92%e8%b5%b7%e5%8f%97%e9%97%9c%e6%b3%a8 |dead-url=no }}{{paywall}}</ref><ref name="Economist">{{Cite news|author=|first=|date=2020-05-23|title=Why some protesters in America wear Hawaiian shirts|work=《[[经济学人|经济学人]]》杂志|url=https://www.economist.com/united-states/2020/05/23/why-some-protesters-in-america-wear-hawaiian-shirts|accessdate=2020-05-30|issn=0013-0613|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200528120822/https://www.economist.com/united-states/2020/05/23/why-some-protesters-in-america-wear-hawaiian-shirts|archivedate=2020-05-28|language=en-gb}}</ref><ref name="Allam-NPR">{{Cite web|title='Boogaloo' Is The New Far-Right Slang For Civil War|url=https://www.npr.org/2020/01/10/795366630/boogaloo-is-the-new-far-right-slang-for-civil-war|accessdate=2020-05-30|author=Allam|date=2020-01-10 |first=Hannah|work=[[全国公共广播电台|全国公共广播电台]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200423033100/https://www.npr.org/2020/01/10/795366630/boogaloo-is-the-new-far-right-slang-for-civil-war|archivedate=2020-04-23|language=en-us}}</ref><ref name="Middlebury">{{Cite web|title=The Boogaloo Movement Wants To Be Seen as Anti-Racist, But It Has a White Supremacist Fringe|url=https://www.middlebury.edu/institute/academics/centers-initiatives/ctec/ctec-publications-0/boogaloo-movement-wants-be-seen-anti-racist|accessdate=2020-06-02|author=Newhouse|date=2020-05-30|first=Alex|work=[[明德大学蒙特雷国际研究学院|明德大学蒙特雷国际研究学院]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200603094223/https://www.middlebury.edu/institute/academics/centers-initiatives/ctec/ctec-publications-0/boogaloo-movement-wants-be-seen-anti-racist|archivedate=2020-06-03}}</ref><ref name="Bellingcat">{{Cite web|title=The Boogaloo Movement Is Not What You Think|url=https://www.bellingcat.com/news/2020/05/27/the-boogaloo-movement-is-not-what-you-think/|accessdate=2020-06-02|author=Evans|date=2020-05-27 |first=Robert|work=Bellingcat|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200528221117/https://www.bellingcat.com/news/2020/05/27/the-boogaloo-movement-is-not-what-you-think/|archivedate=2020-05-28|language=en-us}}</ref><ref name="wapo-june30">{{Cite web|title=Facebook removes hundreds of boogaloo accounts for 'promoting violence' in coordinated takedown|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/technology/2020/06/30/facebook-boogaloo-ban-accounts/|accessdate=2020-07-01|author=Lerman|date=2020-06-30|first=Rachel|work=[[华盛顿邮报|华盛顿邮报]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200701010704/https://www.washingtonpost.com/technology/2020/06/30/facebook-boogaloo-ban-accounts/|archivedate=2020-07-01|language=en-us}}</ref>。该运动也被描述爲[[民兵|民兵]]運動<ref name="BI">{{Cite web|title=Far-right civil war accelerationists called the Boogaloo Bois are appearing at protests around the country with guns and Hawaiian shirts|url=https://www.insider.com/boogaloo-bois-protest-far-right-minneapolis-extremist-guns-hawaiian-shirts-2020-5|accessdate=2020-06-04|author=Goggin|date=2020-06-03|first=Benjamin|work=[[商业内幕|商业内幕]]|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20200605135241/https://www.insider.com/boogaloo-bois-protest-far-right-minneapolis-extremist-guns-hawaiian-shirts-2020-5|archivedate=2020-06-05|language=en-us}}</ref><ref name="Ellis-Wired">{{Cite news|author=Ellis|first=Emma Grey|date=2020-06-18|title=The Meme-Fueled Rise of a Dangerous, Far-Right Militia|work=《[[连线|连线]]》杂志|url=https://www.wired.com/story/boogaloo-movement-protests/|accessdate=2020-06-21|issn=1059-1028|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200619071246/https://www.wired.com/story/boogaloo-movement-protests/|archivedate=2020-06-19|language=en-us}}</ref><ref name="verge1">{{Cite web|title=The Boogaloo movement has successfully hijacked social networks to spread|url=https://www.theverge.com/interface/2020/6/25/21301797/boogaloo-movement-facebook-groups-pages-recommendations-account-bans|accessdate=2020-06-28|author=Newton|date=2020-06-25|first=Casey|work=[[The_Verge|The Verge]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200626170113/https://www.theverge.com/interface/2020/6/25/21301797/boogaloo-movement-facebook-groups-pages-recommendations-account-bans|archivedate=2020-06-26|language=en-us}}</ref>。

“布加洛”一词起源于电影《{{link-en|霹雳舞2：电子布加洛|Breakin' 2: Electric Boogaloo}}》<ref name="xjb1010">{{cite news |author1=陶短房 |title=密谋绑架州长挑起“内战”，美国这个极右翼组织越来越“野” |url=http://www.bjnews.com.cn/feature/2020/10/10/776120.html |accessdate=2020-10-17 |work=[[新京报|新京报]] |date=2020-10-10 |language=zh-cn |archive-date=2020-10-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201017193126/http://www.bjnews.com.cn/feature/2020/10/10/776120.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>，布加洛運動的拥护者说，他們正在準備“美國第二次内戰”或试图煽动“美國第二次内戰”。這樣的舉措被稱作“布加洛”<ref name="VOX2">{{Cite web|title=The 'boogaloo' 'movement,' explained|url=https://www.vox.com/2020/6/8/21276911/boogaloo-explained-civil-war-protests|accessdate=2020-06-09|author=Coaston|date=2020-06-08|first=Jane|work=[[Vox|Vox]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200609170012/https://www.vox.com/2020/6/8/21276911/boogaloo-explained-civil-war-protests|archivedate=2020-06-09|language=en-us}}</ref><ref name="MacFarquhar-NYT">{{Cite news|author=MacFarquhar|first=Neil|author2=Gibbons-Neff|first2=Thomas|date=2020-06-16|title=Air Force Sergeant With Ties to Extremist Group Charged in Federal Officer's Death|work=[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/06/16/us/steven-carrillo-air-force-boogaloo.html |accessdate=2020-06-18 |issn=0362-4331 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200617220913/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/06/16/us/steven-carrillo-air-force-boogaloo.html|archivedate=2020-06-17|language=en-us}}</ref>。2012年，“布加洛”一詞就已在[[貼圖討論版|图像板]]网站[[4chan|4chan]]上使用，但直到2019年末，該詞才引起广泛关注。布加洛運動的拥护者使用“boogaloo”（包括該詞的變體，用以避免社交媒体的過濾）表達「针对联邦政府或左翼政治反对派的暴力起义」的語義。人們估计这会随着政府没收枪支而发生<ref name="Zadrozny-NBC" /><ref name="SPLC">{{Cite web|title='Boogaloo Boy' Arrested in Texas, Charged With Plotting To Murder Cops on Facebook Live|url=https://www.splcenter.org/hatewatch/2020/05/15/boogaloo-boy-arrested-texas-charged-plotting-murder-cops-facebook-live|accessdate=2020-05-30|author=|date=2020-05-15|first=|work=[[南方贫困法律中心|南方贫困法律中心]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200530132346/https://www.splcenter.org/hatewatch/2020/05/15/boogaloo-boy-arrested-texas-charged-plotting-murder-cops-facebook-live|archivedate=2020-05-30|language=en-us}}</ref><ref name=":0">{{Cite news|author=Wilson |first=Jason |date=2020-06-09 |title=Protesters across US attacked by cars driven into crowds and men with guns |work=[[卫报|卫报]]|url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2020/jun/09/protests-us-america-cars-weapons |accessdate=2020-06-09 |issn=0261-3077|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200609102802/https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2020/jun/09/protests-us-america-cars-weapons |archivedate=2020-06-09|language=en}}</ref>。

== 成员架构 ==
该运动組織由[[美國槍支政策|亲枪]]、反政府团体组成<ref name="Zadrozny-NBC" /><ref name="BI" />，但每个小组的意识形态各不相同，对种族等话题的看法也大相径庭<ref name="VOX2" /><ref>{{Cite news|author=Ore|first=Jonathan|date=2020-06-05|title=How the Boogaloo movement rose from an internet joke to an armed movement in the U.S.|work=[[加拿大广播公司|加拿大广播公司]]|url=https://www.cbc.ca/radio/day6/from-little-rock-to-george-floyd-a-poem-for-the-protests-the-boogaloos-pride-during-a-pandemic-and-more-1.5598305/how-the-boogaloo-movement-rose-from-an-internet-joke-to-an-armed-movement-in-the-u-s-1.5598461|accessdate=2020-06-06|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200607000025/https://www.cbc.ca/radio/day6/from-little-rock-to-george-floyd-a-poem-for-the-protests-the-boogaloos-pride-during-a-pandemic-and-more-1.5598305/how-the-boogaloo-movement-rose-from-an-internet-joke-to-an-armed-movement-in-the-u-s-1.5598461|archivedate=2020-06-07|language=en-ca}}</ref><ref name="Sottile">{{Cite news|author=Sottile|first=Leah|date=2020-08-19|url=https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2020/08/19/magazine/boogaloo.html|title=Inside the Boogaloo: America's Extremely Online Extremists|work=纽约时报|accessdate=2020-08-21|archive-date=2020-08-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200821040201/https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2020/08/19/magazine/boogaloo.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。一些[[白人優越主義|白人至上主义者]]<ref name="Charter-Times">{{Cite news|author=Charter|first=David|date=2020-05-16|title='Boogaloo boys' prepare for next American civil war in Hawaiian shirts|work=[[泰晤士报|泰晤士报]]|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/boogaloo-boys-prepare-for-next-american-civil-war-in-hawaiian-shirts-wsmdmmclm|accessdate=2020-05-30|issn=0140-0460|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200528233519/https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/boogaloo-boys-prepare-for-next-american-civil-war-in-hawaiian-shirts-wsmdmmclm|archivedate=2020-05-28}}</ref><ref name="SPLC" />或[[新納粹主義|新纳粹]]团体认为迫在眉睫的动荡将會是一场[[種族衝突|种族战争]]。还有一些团体谴责种族主义和白人至上主义<ref name="RawStory">{{Cite web|title='They want their civil war': Far-right 'boogaloo' militants are embedded in the George Floyd protests in Minneapolis|url=https://www.rawstory.com/2020/05/they-want-their-civil-war-far-right-boogaloo-militants-embedded-themselves-in-the-george-floyd-protests-in-minneapolis/|accessdate=2020-05-30|author=Green|date=2020-05-28|first=Jordan|work=Raw Story|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200529113132/https://www.rawstory.com/2020/05/they-want-their-civil-war-far-right-boogaloo-militants-embedded-themselves-in-the-george-floyd-protests-in-minneapolis/|archivedate=2020-05-29}}</ref>。該組織的絕大多數成員都是[[自由意志主義|自由意志主義者]]，並且反對[[唐納·川普|唐納·川普]]<ref>{{cite news | first1 = Ted | last1 = Hesson | first2 = Ned | last2 = Parker | first3 = Kristina | last3 = Cooke | first4 = Julia | last4 = Harte | title = U.S. Capitol siege emboldens motley crew of extremists | url = https://www.reuters.com/article/usa-election-extremists/us-capitol-siege-emboldens-motley-crew-of-extremists-idUSL1N2JJ0A0 | agency = [[路透社|Reuters]] | date = January 9, 2021 | accessdate = January 19, 2021 | quote = While most “boogaloos” are libertarians who largely oppose Trump, Dunn said the group embraced the moment to strike against the government. | language = en-us | archive-date = 2021-01-12 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210112161521/https://www.reuters.com/article/usa-election-extremists/us-capitol-siege-emboldens-motley-crew-of-extremists-idUSL1N2JJ0A0 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

儘管該運動的某些個人反對種族主義（例如“[[Black_Lives_Matter|Black Lives Matter]]”），但這也引起了研究人员的警惕和怀疑，因为人們不确定這些舉措是否是真实的或是有意掩蓋運動的實際目標<ref name="Middlebury" /><ref name="verge1" />。布加洛运动主要是在网上组织，其参与者参加了包括[[對2019冠狀病毒病疫情應對措施的反抗|2020年美国反封鎖示威]]和[[乔治·弗洛伊德之死引发的示威活动|乔治·弗洛伊德之死引发的示威活动]]。拥有全副武装的布加洛成员常常以其[[夏威夷襯衫|夏威夷襯衫]]的装束和[[軍服|軍服]]来识别<ref name="Owen-Vice">{{Cite web|title=Far-Right Extremists Are Hoping to Turn the George Floyd Protests Into a New Civil War|url=https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/pkyb9b/far-right-extremists-are-hoping-to-turn-the-george-floyd-protests-into-a-new-civil-war|accessdate=2020-05-30|author=Owen|date=2020-05-29|first=Tess|work=[[Vice媒体|Vice媒体]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200530082848/https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/pkyb9b/far-right-extremists-are-hoping-to-turn-the-george-floyd-protests-into-a-new-civil-war|archivedate=2020-05-30|language=en-us}}</ref><ref name="Truscott-Salon">{{Cite web|title=A lynching without a rope has galvanized and divided America — and that's nothing new|url=https://www.salon.com/2020/05/30/a-lynching-without-a-rope--and-in-america-thats-nothing-new/|accessdate=2020-05-30|author=Truscott|date=2020-05-30|first=Lucian K.|work=Salon|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200530134942/https://www.salon.com/2020/05/30/a-lynching-without-a-rope--and-in-america-thats-nothing-new/|archivedate=2020-05-30|language=en-us}}</ref><ref name="AlJazeera">{{Cite web|title=What is the 'Boogaloo' movement?|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/06/boogaloo-movement-200604173050475.html|accessdate=2020-06-06|author=|date=2020-06-05|first=|work=[[半岛电视台英语频道|半岛电视台英语频道]] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200605191906/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/06/boogaloo-movement-200604173050475.html|archivedate=2020-06-05|language=en}}</ref>。

